It’s not supposed to be linezolid or any other real oxazolidinone antibiotic. It is supposed to be a fictional antibiotic in the same family, produced by an anomalous yeast. It was extraordinarily powerful and *unlike* actual oxazolidinone antibiotics such as linezolid, devoid of substantial side effects. In universe the chemical was identified and a mundane chemical synthesis devised, making it an -EX

Edit: one comment, as others have noted, there is actually zero technobabble here. This is written pretty much exactly the way a brief semi-technical overview document describing the same thing would be written in real life for a government research agency. I can easily imagine this as the “abstract” for the whole file describing details of discovery, activity spectrum, structural ID and development of the mundane synthesis.





